</figure>
<ptxt>
Following controls are also performed when A/C switch is ON.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Low speed:
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Cooling fan operates at low speed when A/C refrigerant pressure is more than specified value of 1.1 MPa (11.2 kgf/cm<sup>2</sup>, 160 psi).
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
High speed:
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Cooling fan speed changes from low to high speed when A/C refrigerant pressure exceeds specified value of 1.5 MPa (15.3 kgf/cm<sup>2</sup>, 218 psi).
</ptxt>
<servinfosub id = "AENAP70B1601003001">
<title>
Fail-Safe
</title>
<ptxt>
Cooling fan operates at high speed if malfunction related to ECT sensor is detected.
</ptxt>
</servinfosub>
</servinfo>
</servinfotype>
</configtype>
</servcat>
